title: [JIT] Don't support torch.tensor/Tensor/FloatTensor in Script
body_html:
We are unable to use create tensor using torch.tensor/Tensor/FloatTensor, throw unknown builtin op as below:

======================================================================
ERROR: test_time_sequence_prediction (__main__.TestEndToEndHybridFrontendModels)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "test/test_jit.py", line 4464, in test_time_sequence_prediction
    self.checkTrace(Sequence(), (torch.rand(97, 999),), verbose=True)
  File "/Users/wanchaol/pytorch/torch/jit/__init__.py", line 558, in init_then_register
    self._create_methods(asts, rcbs)
RuntimeError:
unknown builtin op:
@torch.jit.script_method
def forward(self, input, future):
    outputs = []
    h_t = torch.zeros((97, 51), dtype=torch.double)
    c_t = torch.zeros((97, 51), dtype=torch.double)
    h_t2 = torch.zeros((97, 51), dtype=torch.double)
    c_t2 = torch.zeros((97, 51), dtype=torch.double)

    # outputs2 = torch.tensor([], dtype=torch.double)
    outputs2 = torch.Tensor()
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~ <--- HERE
